summary: This document is a court filing from the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case listing juror numbers for peremptory strikes scheduled for November 29, 2021. It provides the juror numbers assigned to two courtrooms (506 and 110) for the jury selection process.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Named as the defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Jury Selection for Peremptory Strikes
events.description: Scheduled exercise of peremptory strikes in the Ghislaine Maxwell trial, with 58 total jurors listed across two courtrooms.

locations: United States District Court Southern District of New York
keyFacts: The document is part of the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20-CR-330).
Jury selection was ongoing on November 29, 2021, with peremptory strikes scheduled.
Fifty-eight total jurors were listed for selection across two courtrooms (506 and 110).
The document lists specific juror numbers for the peremptory strike process.
